info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 09 at 1:34PM MST until January 10 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...Eastern Platte and central Laramie counties including the cities of Wheatland and Cheyenne. * WHEN...Until 2 PM MST Wednesday. The strongest winds are expected overnight into Wednesday morning. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
